<h1 id="main">Command Line Reference</h1>

<p>Phrozn executable <code>phr</code> comes with extensive documentation by itself. When in doubt:</p>
<pre>
    $ phr help
    usage: phrozn &lt;command&gt; [options] [args]
    
    Type 'phrozn help &lt;command&gt;' for help on a specific command.
    Type 'phrozn ? help' for help on using help.
    Type 'phrozn --version' to see the program version and installed plugins.
</pre>

<p class="note">You can use <code>phr</code> and <code>phrozn</code> executables interchangeably. Personally, I prefer much shorter <code>phr</code> alternative.</p>

<h2 id="help">phr help</h2>
<p>To get help reference on particular command use <code>phr help &lt;command&gt;</code> or, bit shorter, <code>phr ? &lt;command&gt;</code></p>

<p>So to get help on using <code>help</code> command:</p>
<pre>
    $ phr ? help
</pre>

<h2 id="phr-init">phr init</h2>
<p>This command is used to initilize your Phrozn project. It creates all necesary folder structure and config files.</p>
<p>For further info use <code>phr ? init</code>.</p>

<h2 id="phr-up">phr update</h2>
<p>For further info use <code>phr ? up</code>.</p>

<h2 id="phr-clobber">phr clobber</h2>
<p>For further info use <code>phr ? clobber</code>.</p>

